==English==

===Etymology===
Compare French ''abandonnement'', from ''abandonner,'' to abandon, relinquish; ''abandonner'' was originally equivalent to ''mettre à bandon,'' to leave to the jurisdiction, i.e. of another, ''bandon'' being from Low Latin ''bandum, bannum,'' order, decree, "ban" (''etymology from [http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Abandonment&oldid=234543 Wikipedia:Abandonment]'')

===Pronunciation===
* ([[RP]]) {{IPA|/əˈbændənmənt/}}
